Package: ProtPQN
Type: Package
Title: Protein-Specific Probabilistic Quotient Normalization for Affinity Proteomics Data From Liquid Biopsies
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Hampus", "Hagelin", email = "hampus.hagelin@scilifelab.se", role = c("aut")),
  person("Leo", "Dahl", email = "leo.dahl@scilifelab.se", role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person("Annika", "Bendes", role = c("ctb")),
  person("Jochen", "Schwenk", role = c("ctb")),
  person("Mun-Gwan", "Hong", role = c("aut")))
Description: Apply Protein-specific Probabilistic Quotient Normalization (ProtPQN) to affinity proteomics data from liquid biopsies.
    Use on any wide-format matrix or data frame containing protein measurements,
    or use a wrapper function to apply on wide or long data with options for transforming back from
    log-scale data before normalization and normalization in a panel/kit-wise manner.
    The normalization method is based on Probabilistic Quotient Normalization (Dieterle et al., 2006).
